{
  "texts": [
    "The process is summarized as follows (Fig. 2a).",
    "At the beginning of deposition, the vapor flux evaporated by the electron beam reaches the substrate and forms a number of randomly dispersed nuclei.",
    "As the nuclei gradually grow, self-shadow regions are formed in the blocked area where additional vapor flux cannot reach due to the height of the nuclei, and nanorods grow in an inclined direction.",
    "Additionally, when rotation is applied in a tilted state, the nanorods are aligned in a perpendicular direction to the substrate.",
    "During subsequent heat treatment, the deposited bimetallic nanolayers of transition metals (Co, Ni, Cu) and noble metals (Pt, Pd, Au) agglomerate together and are decorated in the form of nanoparticles on the SnO 2 nanorods."
  ]
}